.TH MWMC 1 mwmc\-VERSION
.SH NAME
mwmc \- control client for mwm
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mwmc
.I command
.RI [ args ...]
.br
.B mwmc
.RB [ \-h | \-\-help ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mwmc
sends a single command to a running
.BR mwm (1)
instance and prints any reply. It talks to mwm over an X11 ClientMessage IPC
channel: the argument vector is stashed on a throwaway window, mwm is poked with
a ClientMessage, and mwmc blocks (with a short timeout) for the reply mwm writes
back onto that window.
.PP
mwm itself has no built\-in keybindings, so
.B mwmc
is the way every action is triggered \(em typically bound to keys with an
external hotkey daemon such as
.BR sxhkd (1).
.PP
Many commands operate on a hierarchy where a
.B window
belongs to a
.B tag
and a tag is owned by a
.BR monitor .
Most selectors accept the literal words
.B next
or
.B prev
for relative motion, or an explicit name/index.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
print the command summary to stderr and exit. (The same summary is produced by
.BR "mwmc help" ,
which asks mwm directly.)
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Focus
.TP
.B focus next|prev|last
focus the next, previous, or last\-used window in the stack.
.TP
.B focus win next|prev|last|\fIclass\fB
focus a window by direction, last\-used, or by matching its
.B WM_CLASS
.RI ( class
is a case\-insensitive substring).
.TP
.B focus tag next|prev|\fIname\fB
view a tag by direction, name, or 1\-based index.
.TP
.B focus mon next|prev|\fIn\fB
focus a monitor by direction or index.
.SS Move
.TP
.B move win next|prev|master|\fItag\fB
send the focused window to an adjacent tag, promote it to master, or send it to
a named/numbered tag.
.TP
.B move win mon next|prev
send the focused window to the next/previous monitor.
.TP
.B move tag next|prev|\fImon\fB
move the current tag (and its windows) to another monitor.
.SS Layout and sizing
.TP
.B swap next|prev
reorder the focused window forward/backward in the stack.
.TP
.B layout cols|stack|float|next|prev
set or cycle the layout.
.TP
.B master +1|\-1|\fIn\fB
adjust the number of windows in the master area.
.TP
.B master ratio +0.05|\-0.05|\fIf\fB
adjust the master area width fraction.
.TP
.B gap +5|\-5|\fIpx\fB
adjust the gap size, relative or absolute.
.SS Bar and tray
.TP
.B bar toggle|show|hide
toggle, show, or hide the bar.
.TP
.B traybar toggle|show|hide
toggle, show, or hide the system tray. While hidden, mwm keeps owning the tray
selection, so icons still dock and reappear when shown again.
.SS Windows
.TP
.B win close
close the focused window.
.TP
.B win tag \fIname\fB
move the focused window to a named/numbered tag.
.TP
.B win toggle float|full|sticky
toggle the floating, fullscreen, or sticky state of the focused window.
.TP
.B win move \fIdx dy\fB
nudge a floating window by the given pixel offsets (auto\-floats it first).
.TP
.B win resize \fIdw dh\fB
grow/shrink a floating window by the given pixel deltas.
.TP
.B win center
center a floating window on its monitor.
.SS Introspection and session
.TP
.B query tags|windows|monitors|layout|state
print machine\-readable state for scripts, menus, and external keybinders.
.TP
.B reload
re\-read Xresources (xrdb) and restyle the running instance live.
.TP
.B quit
ask mwm to exit.
.TP
.B version
print the running mwm version.
.TP
.B help
print the command summary (reply comes from mwm).
.TP
.B completions bash|zsh
print a shell completion script (embedded in the binary at build time) to
standard output. This needs no running mwm. Redirect it to the location your
shell loads completions from, e.g.:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mwmc completions bash > ~/.local/share/bash-completion/completions/mwmc
mwmc completions zsh  > ~/.zsh/completions/_mwmc   # dir must be in $fpath
.fi
.RE
.IP
Alternatively, source it directly from your shell rc:
.B "source <(mwmc completions bash)" .
.SH MOUSE
With the pointer over a window, hold
.B Super
and drag with the left button to move it, or with the right button to resize it
(the modifier is the
.B movemod
config option). Both gestures auto\-float the window.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B mwmc
exits 0 on success. It exits non\-zero if mwm replies with a line beginning
.BR error: ,
if no reply arrives before the timeout (mwm not running), or on a usage error.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS
.nf
mwmc focus tag web
mwmc move win master
mwmc layout stack
mwmc traybar toggle
mwmc query state
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mwm (1),
.BR sxhkd (1)
